{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"This is a wheat bread, a whole wheat bread,"},{"time":2000,"text":"and it's made with a new technique"},{"time":4000,"text":"that I've been playing around with,"},{"time":6000,"text":"and developing and writing about which, for lack of a better name,"},{"time":8000,"text":"we call the epoxy method."},{"time":10000,"text":"And I call it an epoxy method because --"},{"time":12000,"text":"it's not very appetizing. I understand that --"},{"time":14000,"text":"but -- but"},{"time":16000,"text":"if you think about epoxy, what's epoxy?"},{"time":18000,"text":"It's two resins that are, sort of,"},{"time":20000,"text":"in and of themselves -- neither of which can make glue,"},{"time":23000,"text":"but when you put the two together,"},{"time":25000,"text":"something happens. A bond takes place,"},{"time":26000,"text":"and you get this very strong, powerful"},{"time":28000,"text":"adhesive."},{"time":30000,"text":"Well, in this technique,"},{"time":32000,"text":"what I've tried to do is kind of"},{"time":34000,"text":"gather all of the knowledge that the bread-baking world,"},{"time":36000,"text":"the artisan bread-baking community,"},{"time":38000,"text":"has been trying to accumulate over the last 20 years or so --"},{"time":41000,"text":"since we've been engaged in a bread renaissance in America --"},{"time":44000,"text":"and put it together to come up with a method"},{"time":47000,"text":"that would help to take whole-grain breads."},{"time":50000,"text":"And let's face it, everyone's trying to move towards whole grains."},{"time":53000,"text":"We finally, after 40 years of knowing"},{"time":56000,"text":"that wholegrain was a healthier option,"},{"time":58000,"text":"we're finally getting to the point where we actually are tipping over"},{"time":61000,"text":"and attempting to actually eat them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":63000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":65000,"text":"The challenge, though, for a wholegrain baker is,"},{"time":67000,"text":"you know, how do you make it taste good?"},{"time":70000,"text":"Because whole grain -- it's easy with white flour"},{"time":72000,"text":"to make a good-tasting bread. White flour is sweet."},{"time":75000,"text":"It's mainly starch, and starch, when you break it down --"},{"time":78000,"text":"what is starch? It's -- thank you -- sugar, yes."},{"time":81000,"text":"So a baker, and a good baker,"},{"time":83000,"text":"knows how to pull or draw forth"},{"time":86000,"text":"the inherent sugar trapped in the starch."},{"time":89000,"text":"With whole grain bread, you have other obstacles."},{"time":91000,"text":"You've got bran, which is probably the healthiest part of the bread for us,"},{"time":94000,"text":"or the fiber for us because it is just loaded with fiber,"},{"time":97000,"text":"for the bran is fiber."},{"time":99000,"text":"It's got germ. Those are the good things,"},{"time":101000,"text":"but those aren't the tastiest parts of the wheat."},{"time":103000,"text":"So whole grain breads historically"},{"time":106000,"text":"have had sort of this onus of being health food breads,"},{"time":108000,"text":"and people don't like to eat,"},{"time":110000,"text":"quote, health food. They like to eat healthy and healthily,"},{"time":113000,"text":"but when we think of something as a health food,"},{"time":115000,"text":"we think of it as something we eat out of obligation,"},{"time":118000,"text":"not out of passion and love for the flavor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":121000,"text":"And ultimately, the challenge of the baker,"},{"time":124000,"text":"the challenge of every culinary student, of every chef,"},{"time":126000,"text":"is to deliver flavor."},{"time":129000,"text":"Flavor is king. Flavor rules."},{"time":131000,"text":"I call it the flavor rule. Flavor rules."},{"time":133000,"text":"And -- and"},{"time":135000,"text":"you can get somebody to eat something that's good for them once,"},{"time":138000,"text":"but they won't eat it again if they don't like it, right?"},{"time":141000,"text":"So, this is the challenge for this bread."},{"time":143000,"text":"We're going to try this at lunch, and"},{"time":145000,"text":"I'll explain a bit more about it,"},{"time":147000,"text":"but it's made not only with two types of pre-doughs --"},{"time":150000,"text":"this attempt, again, at bringing out flavor"},{"time":152000,"text":"is to make a piece of dough"},{"time":154000,"text":"the day before that is not leavened."},{"time":157000,"text":"It's just dough that is wet."},{"time":159000,"text":"It's hydrated dough we call \"the soaker\" --"},{"time":161000,"text":"that helps to start enzyme activity."},{"time":163000,"text":"And enzymes are the secret, kind of, ingredient in dough"},{"time":166000,"text":"that brings out flavor."},{"time":168000,"text":"It starts to release the sugars trapped in the starch."},{"time":170000,"text":"That's what enzymes are doing."},{"time":172000,"text":"And so, if we can release some of those,"},{"time":174000,"text":"they become accessible to us in our palate."},{"time":176000,"text":"They become accessible to the yeast as food."},{"time":179000,"text":"They become accessible to the oven for caramelization"},{"time":182000,"text":"to give us a beautiful crust."}]},{"cues":[{"time":184000,"text":"The other pre-dough"},{"time":186000,"text":"that we make is fermented -- our pre-ferment."},{"time":188000,"text":"And it's made -- it can be a sourdough starter, or what we call a \"biga\""},{"time":191000,"text":"or any other kind of pre-fermented dough with a little yeast in it,"},{"time":194000,"text":"and that starts to develop flavor also."},{"time":197000,"text":"And on day two, we put those two pieces together. That's the epoxy."},{"time":200000,"text":"And we're hoping that, sort of, the"},{"time":202000,"text":"enzyme piece of dough"},{"time":204000,"text":"becomes the fuel pack for the leavened piece of dough,"},{"time":207000,"text":"and when we put them together and add the final ingredients,"},{"time":210000,"text":"we can create a bread that does evoke"},{"time":212000,"text":"the full potential of flavor trapped in the grain."},{"time":215000,"text":"That's the challenge. Okay, so, now, what we --"},{"time":217000,"text":"in the journey of wheat, let's go back and look at these 12 stages."}]},{"cues":[{"time":221000,"text":"I'm going to go through them very quickly and then revisit them."},{"time":223000,"text":"Okay, we're going to start with the first stage."},{"time":227000,"text":"And this is what every student has to begin with."},{"time":230000,"text":"Everyone who works in the culinary world knows that"},{"time":232000,"text":"the first stage of cooking is \"mise en place,\""},{"time":235000,"text":"which is just a French way of saying, \"get organized.\""},{"time":240000,"text":"Everything in its place. First stage."},{"time":243000,"text":"So in baking we call it scaling -- weighing out the ingredients."},{"time":245000,"text":"Stage two is mixing. We take the ingredients and we mix them."},{"time":248000,"text":"We have to develop the gluten."},{"time":250000,"text":"There's no gluten in flour. There's only the potential for gluten."},{"time":253000,"text":"Here's another kind of prefiguring of epoxy"},{"time":256000,"text":"because we've got glutenin and gliadin,"},{"time":258000,"text":"neither of which are strong enough to make a good bread."},{"time":261000,"text":"But when they get hydrated and they bond to each other,"},{"time":264000,"text":"they create a stronger molecule, a stronger protein we call gluten."},{"time":268000,"text":"And so we, in the mixing process,"},{"time":270000,"text":"have to develop the gluten,"},{"time":272000,"text":"we have to activate the leaven or the yeast,"},{"time":275000,"text":"and we have to essentially distribute all the ingredients evenly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278000,"text":"Then we get into fermentation, the third stage,"},{"time":280000,"text":"which is really where the flavor develops. \n\n"},{"time":282000,"text":"The yeast comes alive and starts eating the sugars,"},{"time":285000,"text":"creating carbon dioxide and alcohol --"},{"time":287000,"text":"essentially it's burping and sweating, which is what bread is."},{"time":290000,"text":"It's yeast burps and sweat."},{"time":292000,"text":"And somehow, this is transformed --"},{"time":294000,"text":"the yeast burps and sweats are later transformed --"},{"time":297000,"text":"and this is really getting to the heart of what makes bread so special"},{"time":300000,"text":"is that it is a transformational food,"},{"time":302000,"text":"and we're going to explore that in a minute."},{"time":304000,"text":"But then, quickly through the next few stages."},{"time":306000,"text":"We, after it's fermented and it's developed,"},{"time":308000,"text":"started to develop flavor and character,"},{"time":310000,"text":"we divide it into smaller units."},{"time":312000,"text":"And then we take those units and we shape them. We give them a little pre-shape,"},{"time":315000,"text":"usually a round or a little torpedo shape, sometimes."},{"time":318000,"text":"That's called \"rounding.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":320000,"text":"And there's a short rest period. It can be for a few seconds."},{"time":323000,"text":"It can be for 20 or 30 minutes. We call that resting or benching."},{"time":326000,"text":"Then we go into final shaping,"},{"time":328000,"text":"\"panning\" -- which means putting the shaped loaf on a pan."},{"time":332000,"text":"This takes a second, but it's a distinctive stage."},{"time":336000,"text":"It can be in a basket. It can be in a loaf pan, but we pan it."},{"time":340000,"text":"And then, stage nine."},{"time":342000,"text":"The fermentation which started at stage three is continuing"},{"time":345000,"text":"through all these other stages. Again, developing more flavor."},{"time":348000,"text":"The final fermentation takes place in stage nine."},{"time":350000,"text":"We call it \"proofing.\""},{"time":352000,"text":"Proofing means to prove that the dough is alive."},{"time":355000,"text":"And at stage nine we get the dough to the final shape,"},{"time":358000,"text":"and it goes into the oven -- stage 10."},{"time":360000,"text":"Three transformations take place in the oven."},{"time":363000,"text":"The sugars in the dough caramelize in the crust."},{"time":366000,"text":"They give us that beautiful brown crust."},{"time":368000,"text":"Only the crust can caramelize. It's the only place that gets hot enough."},{"time":371000,"text":"Inside, the proteins --"},{"time":373000,"text":"this gluten -- coagulates."},{"time":375000,"text":"When it gets to about 160 degrees,"},{"time":377000,"text":"the proteins all line up \nand they create structure,"},{"time":379000,"text":"the gluten structure --"},{"time":381000,"text":"what ultimately we will call the crumb of the bread."},{"time":384000,"text":"And the starches, when they reach about 180 degrees,"},{"time":386000,"text":"gelatinize."}]},{"cues":[{"time":388000,"text":"And gelatinization is yet another"},{"time":391000,"text":"oven transformation."},{"time":393000,"text":"Coagulation, caramelization and gelatinization --"},{"time":396000,"text":"when the starch is thick and they absorb all the moisture that's around them,"},{"time":399000,"text":"they -- they kind of swell, and then they burst."},{"time":402000,"text":"And they burst, and they spill their guts into the bread."},{"time":405000,"text":"So basically now we're eating yeast sweats --"},{"time":407000,"text":"sweat, burps and starch guts."},{"time":410000,"text":"Again, transformed in stage 10 in the oven"},{"time":413000,"text":"because what went into the oven as dough"},{"time":416000,"text":"comes out in stage 11 as bread."},{"time":419000,"text":"And stage 11, we call it cooling --"},{"time":421000,"text":"because we never really eat the bread right away."},{"time":423000,"text":"There's a little carry-over baking."},{"time":425000,"text":"The proteins have to set up, strengthen and firm up."},{"time":429000,"text":"And then we have stage 12, which the textbooks call \"packaging,\""},{"time":433000,"text":"but my students call \"eating.\""},{"time":435000,"text":"And so, we're going to be on our own journey today from wheat to eat,"},{"time":438000,"text":"and in a few minutes we will try this,"},{"time":440000,"text":"and see if we have succeeded"},{"time":443000,"text":"in fulfilling this baker's mission of pulling out flavor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":446000,"text":"But I want to go back now and revisit these steps,"},{"time":449000,"text":"and talk about it from the standpoint of transformation,"},{"time":451000,"text":"because I really believe that"},{"time":453000,"text":"all things can be understood --"},{"time":456000,"text":"and this is not my own idea. This goes back to the Scholastics and to the Ancients --"},{"time":459000,"text":"that all things can be understood on four levels:"},{"time":461000,"text":"the literal, the metaphoric or poetic level,"},{"time":465000,"text":"the political or ethical level."},{"time":468000,"text":"And ultimately, the mystical or sometimes called the \"anagogical\" level."},{"time":472000,"text":"It's hard to get to those levels unless you go through the literal."},{"time":475000,"text":"In fact, Dante says you can't understand the three deeper levels"},{"time":478000,"text":"unless you first understand the literal level,"},{"time":481000,"text":"so that's why we're talking literally about bread."},{"time":483000,"text":"But let's kind of look at these stages again"},{"time":485000,"text":"from the standpoint of connections to possibly a deeper level --"},{"time":489000,"text":"all in my quest for answering the question,"},{"time":491000,"text":"\"What is it about bread that's so special?\""},{"time":494000,"text":"And fulfilling this mission of evoking the full potential of flavor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":498000,"text":"Because what happens is,"},{"time":500000,"text":"bread begins as wheat or any other grain."},{"time":503000,"text":"But what's wheat? Wheat is a grass"},{"time":505000,"text":"that grows in the field."},{"time":507000,"text":"And, like all grasses, at a certain point it puts out seeds."},{"time":511000,"text":"And we harvest those seeds, and those are the wheat kernels."},{"time":514000,"text":"Now, in order to harvest it -- I mean, what's harvesting?"},{"time":516000,"text":"It's just a euphemism for killing, right?"},{"time":520000,"text":"I mean, that's what's harvest -- we say we harvest the pig, you know?"},{"time":522000,"text":"Yes, we slaughter, you know. Yes, that's life."},{"time":525000,"text":"We harvest the wheat,"},{"time":527000,"text":"and in harvesting it, we kill it."},{"time":529000,"text":"Now, wheat is alive,"},{"time":531000,"text":"and as we harvest it, it gives up its seeds."},{"time":535000,"text":"Now, at least with seeds we have the potential for future life."},{"time":538000,"text":"We can plant those in the ground."},{"time":540000,"text":"And we save some of those for the next generation."},{"time":542000,"text":"But most of those seeds get crushed"},{"time":544000,"text":"and turned into flour."},{"time":546000,"text":"And at that point, the wheat has suffered the ultimate indignity."},{"time":549000,"text":"It's not only been killed,"},{"time":551000,"text":"but it's been denied any potential for creating future life."},{"time":554000,"text":"So we turn it into flour."}]},{"cues":[{"time":557000,"text":"So as I said, I think bread is a transformational food."},{"time":560000,"text":"The first transformation -- and, by the way,"},{"time":563000,"text":"the definition of transformation for me is"},{"time":565000,"text":"a radical change from one thing into something else."},{"time":568000,"text":"O.K.? Radical, not subtle."},{"time":570000,"text":"Not like hot water made cold,"},{"time":572000,"text":"or cold water turned hot,"},{"time":574000,"text":"but water boiled off and becoming steam."},{"time":577000,"text":"That's a transformation, two different things."},{"time":579000,"text":"Well, in this case, the first transformation"},{"time":581000,"text":"is alive to dead."},{"time":584000,"text":"I'd call that radical."},{"time":587000,"text":"So, we've got now this flour."},{"time":590000,"text":"And what do we do? We add some water."},{"time":592000,"text":"In stage one, we weigh it."},{"time":594000,"text":"In stage two, we add water and salt to it, mix it together,"},{"time":596000,"text":"and we create something that we call \"clay.\""},{"time":598000,"text":"It's like clay."},{"time":600000,"text":"And we infuse that clay"},{"time":602000,"text":"with an ingredient that we call \"leaven.\""},{"time":605000,"text":"In this case, it's yeast, but yeast is leaven. What does leaven mean?"},{"time":608000,"text":"Leaven comes from the root word that means enliven --"},{"time":612000,"text":"to vivify, to bring to life."},{"time":616000,"text":"By the way, what's the Hebrew word for clay? Adam."},{"time":620000,"text":"You see, the baker, in this moment,"},{"time":622000,"text":"has become, in a sense,"},{"time":624000,"text":"sort of, the God of his dough, you know, and his dough, well,"},{"time":627000,"text":"while it's not an intelligent life form, is now alive."},{"time":630000,"text":"And we know it's alive because in stage three,"},{"time":632000,"text":"it grows. Growth is the proof of life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":635000,"text":"And while it's growing, all these"},{"time":637000,"text":"literal transformations are taking place."},{"time":639000,"text":"Enzymes are breaking forth sugars."},{"time":641000,"text":"Yeast is eating sugar and"},{"time":643000,"text":"turning it into carbon dioxide and alcohol."},{"time":646000,"text":"Bacteria is in there, eating the same sugars,"},{"time":648000,"text":"turning them into acids."},{"time":650000,"text":"In other words, personality and character's being developed in this dough\n\n"},{"time":653000,"text":"under the watchful gaze of the baker."},{"time":656000,"text":"And the baker's choices all along the way"},{"time":658000,"text":"determine the outcome of the product."},{"time":662000,"text":"A subtle change in temperature -- a subtle change in time --"},{"time":665000,"text":"it's all about a balancing act between time, temperature"},{"time":667000,"text":"and ingredients. That's the art of baking."},{"time":669000,"text":"So all these things are determined by the baker,"},{"time":671000,"text":"and the bread goes through some stages, and characters develop."},{"time":674000,"text":"And then we divide it, and this one big piece of dough"},{"time":676000,"text":"is divided into smaller units, and each of those units"},{"time":678000,"text":"are given shape by the baker."},{"time":680000,"text":"And as they're shaped, they're raised again,"},{"time":682000,"text":"all along proving that they're alive,"},{"time":684000,"text":"and developing character."}]},{"cues":[{"time":686000,"text":"And at stage 10, we take it to the oven."},{"time":689000,"text":"It's still dough. Nobody eats bread dough --"},{"time":691000,"text":"a few people do, I think, but not too many."},{"time":693000,"text":"I've met some dough eaters, but --"},{"time":695000,"text":"it's not the staff of life, right? Bread is the staff of life."},{"time":699000,"text":"But dough is what we're working with,"},{"time":701000,"text":"and we take that dough to the oven,"},{"time":703000,"text":"and it goes into the oven. As soon as the interior temperature of that dough"},{"time":707000,"text":"crosses the threshold of 140 degrees,"},{"time":709000,"text":"it passes what we call the \"thermal death point.\""},{"time":714000,"text":"Students love that TDP. They think it's the name of a video game."},{"time":717000,"text":"But it's the thermal death point -- all life ceases there."},{"time":720000,"text":"The yeast, whose mission it has been up till now to raise the dough,"},{"time":724000,"text":"to enliven it, to vivify it,"},{"time":726000,"text":"in order to complete its mission,"},{"time":728000,"text":"which is also to turn this dough into bread,"},{"time":730000,"text":"has to give up its life."},{"time":732000,"text":"So you see the symbolism at work? It's starting to come forth a little bit, you know."},{"time":735000,"text":"It's starting to make sense to me --"},{"time":739000,"text":"what goes in is dough,"},{"time":741000,"text":"what comes out is bread --"},{"time":743000,"text":"or it goes in alive,"},{"time":745000,"text":"comes out dead."},{"time":747000,"text":"Third transformation. First transformation, alive to dead."},{"time":750000,"text":"Second transformation, dead brought back to life."},{"time":754000,"text":"Third transformation, alive to dead --"},{"time":756000,"text":"but dough to bread."}]},{"cues":[{"time":759000,"text":"Or another analogy would be,"},{"time":761000,"text":"a caterpillar has been turned into a butterfly."},{"time":764000,"text":"And it's what comes out of the oven"},{"time":766000,"text":"that is what we call the staff of life."},{"time":769000,"text":"This is the product"},{"time":771000,"text":"that"},{"time":774000,"text":"everyone in the world eats, that is so difficult to give up."},{"time":778000,"text":"It's so"},{"time":780000,"text":"deeply embedded in our psyches that"},{"time":783000,"text":"bread is used as a symbol for life."},{"time":786000,"text":"It's used as a symbol for transformation."},{"time":791000,"text":"And so, as we get to stage 12 and we partake of that,"},{"time":794000,"text":"again completing the life cycle,"},{"time":797000,"text":"you know, we have a chance to essentially ingest that --"},{"time":800000,"text":"it nurtures us, and we continue to carry on"},{"time":803000,"text":"and have opportunities to ponder"},{"time":805000,"text":"things like this."},{"time":807000,"text":"So this is what I've learned from bread."},{"time":809000,"text":"This is what bread has taught me in my journey."},{"time":812000,"text":"And what we're going to attempt to do"},{"time":814000,"text":"with this bread here, again,"},{"time":816000,"text":"is to use, in addition to everything we talked about,"},{"time":819000,"text":"this bread we're going to call \"spent grain bread\""},{"time":822000,"text":"because, as you know, bread-making is very similar to beer-making."},{"time":825000,"text":"Beer is basically liquid bread,"},{"time":827000,"text":"or bread is solid beer."},{"time":829000,"text":"And --"},{"time":831000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":832000,"text":"they -- they're invented around the same time. I think beer came first."},{"time":835000,"text":"And the Egyptian who was tending the beer fell asleep"},{"time":838000,"text":"in the hot, Egyptian sun, and it turned into bread."}]},{"cues":[{"time":840000,"text":"But we've got this bread,"},{"time":842000,"text":"and what I did here is to try to, again,"},{"time":844000,"text":"evoke even more flavor from this grain,"},{"time":848000,"text":"was we've added into it the spent grain from beer-making."},{"time":851000,"text":"And if you make this bread, you can use any kind of spent grain from any type of beer."},{"time":855000,"text":"I like dark spent grain. Today we're using a light spent grain"},{"time":858000,"text":"that's actually from, like, some kind of a lager of some sort --"},{"time":861000,"text":"a light lager or an ale -- that is wheat and barley that's been toasted."},{"time":865000,"text":"In other words, the beer-maker knows also how to evoke flavor from the grains"},{"time":868000,"text":"by using sprouting and malting and roasting."},{"time":871000,"text":"We're going to take some of that, and put it into the bread."},{"time":873000,"text":"So now we not only have a high-fiber bread,"},{"time":876000,"text":"but now fiber on top of fiber."},{"time":878000,"text":"And so this is, again, hopefully"},{"time":881000,"text":"not only a healthy bread,"},{"time":883000,"text":"but a bread that you will enjoy."},{"time":885000,"text":"So, if I, kind of, break this bread,"},{"time":888000,"text":"maybe we can share this now a little bit here."},{"time":891000,"text":"We'll start a little piece here,"},{"time":893000,"text":"and I'm going to take a little piece here --"},{"time":895000,"text":"I think I'd better taste it myself before you have it at lunch."},{"time":898000,"text":"I'll leave you"},{"time":901000,"text":"with what I call the baker's blessing."},{"time":903000,"text":"May your crust be crisp,"},{"time":905000,"text":"and your bread always rise."},{"time":908000,"text":"Thank you."}]}]}